        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><strong>Probation Officer Protection Act of 2021</strong><strong></strong></p> <p>This bill authorizes a probation officer to arrest a person other than the probationer without a warrant if there is probable cause to believe the person forcibly assaulted or obstructed a probation officer engaged in the performance of official duties.<br /> </p>]]>
        </text>
